{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"tool_MqWsOyX6Jk08zRf8VXoDm1j9","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Rusty's Retirement Steam game 2666330 developer features gameplay review 2024 2025\"\n\nSearch results for query: Rusty's Retirement Steam game 2666330 developer Rusty's Retirement Steam game 2666330 gameplay review Rusty's Retirement Steam game 2666330 features 2024\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Review | Rusty's Retirement (PC)\",\"url\":\"https://questdaily.com.au/review/review-rustys-retirement-pc/\"},{\"title\":\"How Rusty's Retirement idle-farmed its way to 300k+ Steam sales!\",\"url\":\"https://newsletter.gamediscover.co/p/how-rustys-retirement-idle-farmed\"},{\"title\":\"Review: Rusty's Retirement is a well-oiled idle farming sim\",\"url\":\"https://www.comfycozygaming.com/2024/05/03/rustys-retirement-review/\"},{\"title\":\"System requirements - Rusty's Retirement Wiki - Fandom\",\"url\":\"https://rustys-retirement.fandom.com/wiki/Rusty%27s_Retirement\"},{\"title\":\"Rusty’s Retirement is a relaxing cautionary tale that sits at the bottom of your screen\",\"url\":\"https://bigbossbattle.com/rustys-retirement-review/\"},{\"title\":\"Mister Morris Games - Steam Developer\",\"url\":\"https://store.steampowered.com/developer/MisterMorrisGames/\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's a comprehensive overview of **Rusty's Retirement** (Steam App ID: 2666330):\n\n## Developer & Release Info\n- **Developer/Publisher:** Mister Morris Games (a solo indie dev, Jordan Morris)\n- **Engine:** Unity\n- **Release Date:** April 26, 2024\n- **Price:** $6.99 USD (base game), with a $4 Supporter Pack DLC (golden outfit for Rusty)\n- **Platform:** PC (Windows/Mac) via Steam\n\n## Key Features\n- **Desktop-Integrated Idle Play:** The game's signature feature is its \"bottom-of-screen\" (or side-of-screen) design. It occupies roughly 25–33% of your monitor and sits behind other windows, allowing you to work, browse, or stream while your farm runs in the background.\n- **Low-Stakes Automation:** Nothing bad happens if you ignore it. It caters to both casual players and strategic \"min/max\" idler fans.\n- **Multiple Farms:** After completing the first farm, additional farm types unlock for extended play.\n- **Achievements:** 55 Steam achievements in the full release.\n- **Soundtrack:** Original score by lars asger (7 tracks).\n\n## Gameplay Overview\nRusty's Retirement is an idle farming sim where you play as Rusty, a retired robot resettling a post-apocalyptic Earth (implied to be after a robotic uprising, with human artifacts like cars and wire spools scattered about).\n\n**Core Loop:**\n- **Plant & Harvest:** Start with free seeds, then grow crops to earn coins and biofuel. Different crops have varying grow times, watering needs, and biofuel values.\n- **Automate:** Hire robot helpers (Watering Bots, Harvesting Bots, Biofuel Bots) that run on biofuel.\n- **Unlock Residents:** Welcome additional robots like:\n  - **Splunk:** Auto-seeds empty plots\n  - **Pinion:** Provides farm stats/breakdowns\n  - **Forbic:** Unlocks fruit bushes (\"Bublets\")\n  - **Sonnet:** Sells decorations and crop signposts\n  - **Slate:** Finds fossils to trade for farm animals (pigs, cows)\n- **Priorities:** You can adjust task priorities for Rusty and Haiku (from the dev's previous game, *Haiku, the Robot*) so they focus on watering, harvesting, or moving goods as needed.\n- **Progression:** Unlock new crops by harvesting specific quantities of existing ones. Convert crops to biofuel to power your automation, or convert biofuel to spare parts to speed things up.\n\n## Reception & Reviews (2024)\nThe game has been very well received:\n- **Commercial Success:** Sold approximately **330,000+ copies on Steam** within months of its April 2024 launch, generating significant revenue even at its low price point. The Supporter Pack DLC sold around 36,000 units (~11% attach rate).\n- **Review Scores:** Critics have rated it highly; one review gave it a **9/10** with a \"Cozy Score\" of 10/10.\n- **Critical Praise:** Reviewers highlight its charming pixel art, clever screen-space concept, satisfying automation curve, and \"true idle\" nature where you can eventually reach full automation and simply watch your farm thrive. Many have clocked 100–200+ hours across multiple farms.\n- **Common Critiques:** Some noted the lack of a tutorial (players are \"thrown into the shallow end\") and that late-game progression on the first farm can slow to a slog while waiting for final crop unlocks.\n\n## Why It Stood Out\nJordan Morris originally built Rusty's Retirement as a **2-week prototype** after shipping *Haiku, the Robot*. The game found a unique niche as a productive \"ambient\" companion app—offering dopamine hits and light management without demanding full attention, fitting into the growing trend of games/apps that scale to the player's available focus.\n\n*Note: While most major coverage dates from its 2024 launch window, the game has maintained a strong player base into 2025 through Steam sales and its word-of-mouth reputation as a cozy desktop companion.*\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a372f386-0781-472d-a6e3-928e4f97505b","uuid":"7f41dabe-81b5-403e-a979-1f571128aaca","timestamp":"2026-05-20T10:26:29.326Z","tool_use_result":{"query":"Rusty's Retirement Steam game 2666330 developer features gameplay review 2024 2025","results":["Search results for query: Rusty's Retirement Steam game 2666330 developer Rusty's Retirement Steam game 2666330 gameplay review Rusty's Retirement Steam game 2666330 features 2024",{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_d86oo9harjis73etjorg","content":[{"title":"Review | Rusty's Retirement (PC)","url":"https://questdaily.com.au/review/review-rustys-retirement-pc/"},{"title":"How Rusty's Retirement idle-farmed its way to 300k+ Steam sales!","url":"https